main event: Unidentified objects were observed hovering above Marrowbone Lake near Nashville, Tennessee, on March 19, 1950.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be black, round, about the size of a 300 lb. bomb, and made a noise like wind blowing through trees., Witnesses described the objects as revolving and estimated their speed at 500 miles per hour., The objects were observed between six and twelve o'clock, mainly in the afternoon., The sighting involved two Nashville real estate salesmen who were fishing at the time., Observations could not be mistaken for military aircraft according to a spokesman at Stewart Air Force Base.
